        <!-- Tips -->
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--accent-color);">Tipping Tips</h2>
        <div class="tips-grid">
            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3>Quick Mental Math</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>For 10%: move the decimal point one place left ($50 bill = $5 tip)</li>
                    <li>For 15%: calculate 10% and add half ($50 bill = $5 + $2.50 = $7.50)</li>
                    <li>For 20%: calculate 10% and double it ($50 bill = $5 x 2 = $10)</li>
                    <li>For 25%: calculate 20% and add another 5% ($50 = $10 + $2.50 = $12.50)</li>
                    <li>Round the bill to the nearest $10 first for even easier math</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3>Tipping Etiquette</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Always tip on the pre-tax subtotal — you shouldn't be tipping on the sales tax amount</li>
                    <li>For poor service, talk to the manager instead of leaving no tip — the server may not be at fault</li>
                    <li>Check if gratuity is already included — common for large groups (18–20% auto-gratuity)</li>
                    <li>Tip in cash when possible — it goes directly to the server and is received immediately</li>
                    <li>When abroad, research local customs — tipping is not expected (or even offensive) in many countries</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
